OL,3,CFlood-ravaged communities on the
OL,4,CEngland-Wales border feel left behind
OL,6,FThe increased frequency of flooding is
OL,7,Flinked to climate change, as heavier,
OL,8,Ffiercer storms occur more often than
OL,9,Fthey used to.
OL,11,FTo try and tackle it, various agencies
OL,12,Fcame together, including the
OL,13,FEnvironment Agency, Natural Resources
OL,14,FWales and local authorities, to form
OL,15,Fthe Severn Valley Water Management
OL,16,FScheme.
OL,18,FBut despite being given #10 million
OL,19,Fpounds in funding, more than three
OL,20,Fyears on, local Flood Action Groups
OL,21,Fsay they've yet to see any progress.
